params._raffleData: Structure that contains all the data related to the Raffle

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

postBuyOrder(uint256,uint256,address,uin.notice: Allows users to buy a raffle ticket

params._buyer: Address which the ticket will be assigned to
params._price: Price paid in the buy order. It should be the same as the price of the current sell order,          otherwise it will revert. Used to avoid a seller frontrunning a postBuyOrder() call with a          postSellOrder() call increasing the price

postSellOrder(uint256,uint256,address,ui.notice: Allows users to put their raffle tickets for sale

params._currency: Tickets will be bought with this ERC20 token. address(0) should be put here if the currency will be Matic
params._price: Price per ticket. It can be zero in case of an "airdrop"
